Yes, it is possible to replace letters without using regular expressions. Instead of using the regular expression to replace the letters, you can use JavaScript's built-in string method `replace()`. Here is a modified version of your code that uses the `replace()` method:

```
function main() {
  var sentence = "";
  var lettersToRemove = [];

